# Copy to `.env` and fill in for your domain and API (never commit `.env`).

# --- Site & branding ---
# VITE_SITE_PUBLIC_URL=https://www.yourdomain.com
# VITE_SITE_NAME=Your Brand Name
# VITE_SITE_TITLE=Your Brand — Real estate in Pakistan
# VITE_LOGO_URL=/brand/logo.png

# --- Backend (messages & leads) ---
# Browser posts to `/api/...` unless `VITE_API_BASE_URL` is set.
# - Local: `npm run dev` proxies `/api` → Node on API_PORT.
# - Production: reverse-proxy `https://yourdomain.com/api` → your Node server, OR set:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com   (host root only — routes are /leads/*, /health)
# - Vercel: `vercel.json` routes `/api/*` to `api/index.js` (same Express app as `server/`). Set `MONGODB_URI`,
#   `CORS_ORIGIN`, etc. in the Vercel project Environment Variables (serverless — not only `VITE_*`).
#   List each allowed browser origin (production + preview URLs); `cors` does not accept `*` patterns here.
#
# Optional path overrides (defaults shown):
# VITE_API_CONTACT_PATH=/leads/contact
# VITE_API_CONCIERGE_PATH=/leads/concierge
# VITE_API_NEWSLETTER_PATH=/leads/newsletter
# VITE_API_LAUNCH_INTEREST_PATH=/leads/launch-interest

# --- MongoDB (server only — read by `node server/index.js`, never exposed to the browser) ---
# If your password contains @, #, etc., URL-encode it (e.g. @ → %40).
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USER:PASSWORD@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/vertex?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster0
# MONGODB_DB=vertex
# MONGODB_LEADS_COLLECTION=leads
# MONGODB_PROPERTIES_COLLECTION=properties
# If Node fails with "certificate validation failed" (VPN, antivirus HTTPS scan, Windows CRLF in .env):
# MONGODB_TLS_INSECURE=true
# Alias: MONGODB_TLS_RELAX=true
# Values accept true / 1 / yes (trimmed; fixes Windows CRLF). Restart the server after changing .env.
# Set to true once to import `server/seed-catalog.json` when the properties collection is empty.
# MONGODB_AUTO_SEED=true
# API_PORT=3001
# CORS: server merges env with https://vertexestatepvt.com, https://www.vertexestatepvt.com, localhost:5173.
# Add more origins (comma-separated) if needed:
# CORS_ORIGIN=https://preview-xyz.vercel.app
#
# With `npm run dev`, check Mongo + counts: open http://localhost:5173/api/health in the browser
# (or http://localhost:3001/health). Or run: npm run check-db
# Coming-soon signups land in collection `leads` with
# `source: "coming_soon_launch"` when POST /leads/launch-interest returns 201.

# GET /properties reads collection `properties`. Forms POST to `leads` with JSON bodies like:
# { "source": "contact_page", "name", "email", "phone", "subject", "message", "submittedAt" }
# { "source": "home_concierge", ...form fields..., "submittedAt" }
# { "source": "footer_newsletter", "email", "submittedAt" }
# { "source": "coming_soon_launch", "name", "email", "phone", "description", "submittedAt" }  ← waitlist (Date on server)
# GET /stats/launch-interest-count → { "count": <number> } (public waitlist count; no personal data)

# --- Contact page map (optional; can also set mapEmbedUrl in public/site/contact.json) ---
# VITE_MAP_EMBED_URL=https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=...

# --- Listings catalog (optional until you have a DB API) ---
# Full URL returning a JSON array matching src/types Property (see seed in src/data/properties.ts).
# VITE_PROPERTIES_JSON_URL=https://yourdomain.com/api/properties.json
# Set to false to hide demo listings when using only remote JSON (after URL works).
# VITE_INCLUDE_SEED_PROPERTIES=true

# --- Coming soon (full-screen gate; default ON) ---
# One launch time for every visitor (all browsers / profiles). Set ISO here, or change the
# default in `src/config/siteConfig.ts` (`comingSoonUntilMs` fallback) and rebuild.
# VITE_SHOW_COMING_SOON=false
# VITE_COMING_SOON_UNTIL=2026-08-15T23:59:59+05:00
# Short text next to the coming-soon map pin (default: F7 Markaz, Islamabad):
# VITE_COMING_SOON_LOCATION_LINE=F-7 Markaz, Islamabad
# Optional — override social links on the coming-soon screen (defaults are in siteConfig):
# VITE_SOCIAL_FACEBOOK_URL=https://www.facebook.com/...
# VITE_SOCIAL_INSTAGRAM_URL=https://www.instagram.com/...
# VITE_SOCIAL_TIKTOK_URL=https://www.tiktok.com/@...
# Google Maps — default pin uses coordinates (Chaudhry Plaza, F-7 Markaz). Text search was landing in the wrong sector.
# Nudge the pin (decimal degrees, no quotes):
# VITE_VERTEX_OFFICE_LAT=33.718722
# VITE_VERTEX_OFFICE_LNG=73.054125
# Full “Open in Maps” / contact link (overrides lat/lng when set):
# VITE_COMING_SOON_MAP_URL=https://www.google.com/maps/...
# VITE_VERTEX_OFFICE_MAP_URL=https://www.google.com/maps/...
# Live iframe `src` — best precision: Maps → Share → Embed a map, paste URL here:
# VITE_COMING_SOON_MAP_EMBED_URL=https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=...
# Contact iframe: `VITE_MAP_EMBED_URL` or `public/site/contact.json` mapEmbedUrl

# --- Demo estate owner bootstrap (replace with real auth in production) ---
# VITE_ESTATE_OWNER_EMAIL=owner@yourdomain.com
# VITE_ESTATE_OWNER_PHONE=+92...
# VITE_ESTATE_OWNER_NAME=Your Name
# VITE_ESTATE_OWNER_PASSWORD=change-me
